
messages - system log
secure - ssh attempts into the system 

# To view all the messages that are being appended

 $ tail -f /var/log/messages 

# journald logs all events of our system
# reboot will remove the contents of journald 
# /etc/systemd/journald.conf (journald configuration file) 

$ journalctl -f 

$ journalctl -n (shows last 10 lines) 
$ systemd-analyze blame (how log it takes to boot differnt processes, for troubleshoot)

/etc/rsyslog.conf (log configuration file)

 
